                                                            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.youtube.com/@workoutendomondo"><img alt="youtube"
                                        src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/youtube.svg" /></a>
                                                            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.instagram.com/workoutendomondo/"><img alt="instagram"
                                        src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/instagram-2-1.svg" /></a>
                                                            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.pinterest.com/endomondo/"><img alt="pinterest"
                                        src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pinterest-1.svg" /></a>
                                                            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.newsbreak.com/m/endomondo-306392510"><img alt="newsbreak"
                                        src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/svgexport-2-2-1.svg" /></a>
                                                </div>
                    <div class="exc-description">
                        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Finding the right </span><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-rear-delt-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">rear delt exercises</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for your workout doesn’t need to be challenging. The standing cable rear delt fly is perfect for targeting the posterior deltoids to establish that rounded shoulder physique. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This exercise is a must-add to your training regimen if you want to improve your upper body physique. Being a compound exercise, it targets multiple muscles including the upper trapezius. This promotes healthy movement and range of motion alongside the rear delts. Find out more on how to do the standing cable rear delt fly in this informative guide! </span></p>                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
