                        <div class="muscle-text bd-bot exercise-list-start">
                            <h3><b>Upper Trapezius</b></h3><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The upper trapezius is the smallest section of the broad trapezius muscle. The trapezius muscle is shaped like a flat triangle across the shoulders, neck, and back. The upper trapezius forms the top of the shoulders and the base of the neck. </span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This muscle is necessary for everyday movements. It is responsible for </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK518994/#:~:text=The%20function%20of%20the%20trapezius%20is%20to%20stabilize%20and%20move%20the%20scapula.%20The%20upper%20fibers%20can%20elevate%20and%20upwardly%20rotate%20the%20scapula%20and%20extend%20the%20neck." target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">extending and rotating the neck</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and for lifting the arms. This muscle is used to turn one's head to glance in the car's rear-view mirror and shrug one's shoulders.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The upper trapezius is engaged in the standing cable rear delt fly when the arms lift and draw the cables back. Strengthening this muscle is important for supporting the spine and </span><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10883562/#:~:text=the%20left%20side.-,There%20is%20a%20relationship%20between%20the%20stiffness%20of%20the%20right%20and,is%20likely%20to%20be%20determined%20by%20the%20muscle%20fibre%20stretching%20mechanism.,-Go%20to%3A" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">maintaining healthy posture</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
